cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CY, cs.SE

The paper discusses the security management framework for vehicular networks using 5G technology, which involves communication networks and security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also focuses on credential management and edge-initiated security, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the performance tradeoff, which involves information theory, and hence, it can be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the sustainability of connections, which involves system analysis and design, and hence, it can be categorized under cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper discusses the probability of connectivity, which involves probability and statistics, and hence, it can be categorized under cs.CY (Computational Geometry).
